==English==

===Etymology===
From {{term|bonhomie}}, borrowed from {{etyl|fr}} ''bonhomie''; from {{term|bonhomme}} "good-natured man"; from {{term|bon}} "good" + {{term|homme}} "man". Components akin to {{etyl|en}} {{term|boon}} and {{term|homo}}.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# [[good-natured|Good-natured]]; good-hearted; [[friendly]]; [[genial]]; possessing an [[affable]] and [[approachable]] disposition; easy to talk to.

